1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:01,760
You two are acting strange.

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:04,520
Seriously, are you two fighting?

3
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:08,160
Should I put my arm around his shoulder
to prove that we aren’t on bad terms?

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:11,840
Where is Ko Song?

5
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:13,280
Where is he?

6
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:15,240
Ko Song has been acting strange lately.

7
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:16,600
Are you avoiding me?

8
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:19,160
I’m short-sighted. I can’t see the blackboard.

9
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:20,240
This is what you want, right?

10
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,040
Ko Song.

11
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:24,800
Can’t you just say what is on your mind?

12
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:26,720
I’m sorry.

13
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:45,680
Fine.

14
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:47,960
If you don’t want to talk to me,

15
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,000
then don’t ever speak to me again.

16
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:56,080
I like you.

17
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,680
I know what I did is wrong.

18
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:15,960
I’m scared.

19
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,320
I’m scared that you will hate me
more than you already did.

20
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,640
Why would I hate you?

21
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:30,360
I don’t know.

22
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:33,560
I don’t know what you are thinking.

23
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,240
After I did that,

24
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:38,200
you rushed out.

25
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:40,400
What am I supposed to think?

26
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,400
I don’t want to lose you, Orange.

27
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,880
You’re going to lose me
because you are doing this.

28
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,720
Listen.

29
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,680
I’m neither mad nor hate you.

30
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,840
Can you now tell me

31
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,240
how you feel about me?

32
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:19,720
I…

33
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,000
I’m still your friend.

34
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:33,880
Okay.

35
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,480
Okay.

36
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,880
No, you don’t get it.

37
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,760
Do you really understand what I mean?

38
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,000
I get it.

39
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,360
Are you going to keep your distance from me?

40
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:54,920
No.

41
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,560
Can we go back to being the same, Ko Song?

42
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:16,600
Promise?

43
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,640
(No one understands how I feel
better than I do.)

44
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:46,600
(I keep thinking if it’s the right thing
to say what I’m feeling.)

45
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:09,640
(The society, the social context,
people around me,)

46
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,160
(And the guy in front of me.)

47
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:20,200
(Everything pushes me to overthink.)

48
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,160
Are you okay?

49
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:36,280
(To admit what I am,
it’s not solely my decision.)

50
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:44,440
(The easiest way to save this relationship,)

51
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,240
(it’s to go back to the way we used to be.)

52
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,600
My goodness!

53
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:50,640
What is this?

54
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:54,360
Ko.

55
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,240
Why are you all wet?

56
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,240
It was raining.
How am I supposed to stay dry?

57
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:02,760
That’s a weird question.

58
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,520
You’re getting sarcastic.

59
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:06,200
Hurry and take a shower.

60
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,840
If you get sick and miss school tomorrow,
I’ll punish you.

61
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,080
Yes, ma’am.

62
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,400
You should go take a shower,
otherwise you’ll get sick.

63
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,880
If you’re going to keep looking at him like this,

64
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,400
why don’t you go take a shower at his house?

65
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,520
Mom!

66
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,520
What?

67
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,760
Don’t tell me that
you want to take a day off tomorrow?

68
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,600
No, it’s not that, Mom.

69
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:14,720
So what is it?

70
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:26,720
Just hypothetically.

71
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:28,960
Just hypothetically.

72
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,840
If my friend…

73
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,400
He…

74
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,240
Hey.

75
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:35,920
How long are you going to mumble?

76
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,120
I want to watch the drama.
It’s the final episode.

77
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,040
I want to see how the male lead
confesses his feelings to the female lead.

78
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,760
So spill it.

79
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,120
Okay.

80
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:48,120
If my friend does something
that he’s not supposed to,

81
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,200
but I’m not mad at him.

82
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,600
but I’m not mad at him.

83
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:57,880
We talked, he apologized to me,
and I understand everything.

84
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,480
Is this story fictional or real?

85
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,320
That’s not the point, Mom.

86
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:08,240
Alright.

87
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:11,720
Do you mean it
when you said you weren’t mad?

88
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:29,800
Ko!

89
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:34,120
I wasn’t mad. I was just shocked.

90
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,120
Then just tell him that.

91
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:41,240
I already told him,
but he doesn’t seem to believe it.

92
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:45,560
You just need to tell him seriously.

93
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:54,280
You aren’t upset by what he did.

94
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,720
He doesn’t need to feel guilty.

95
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,720
You are okay now.

96
00:08:58,960 --> 00:08:59,720
Something like this.

97
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,480
You should talk things out with him.

98
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,480
Don’t leave the problem for too long.

99
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:10,680
The longer you leave it unsolved,
the longer he has to live with the guilt.

100
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:15,000
He’s avoiding you
because he feels very guilty.

101
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:19,880
It means that he really cares about you.

102
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,640
Don’t wait for too long.
You should talk it out quickly.

103
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:28,320
Otherwise, you might end up
losing this friend instead of making up.

104
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,640
Ko!

105
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,520
I haven’t finished. Where are you going?

106
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,720
You haven’t told me who you had a fight with.

107
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:44,480
Ko.

108
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:49,840
Ko Song.

109
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:51,680
Ko.

110
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:58,840
I’m really sorry for what happened that night.

111
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,160
Listen.

112
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,000
I’m not mad at you.

113
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,720
You don’t need to be scared of losing me.

114
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:18,240
You promised me that
you wouldn’t disappear again.

115
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,960
Don’t break your promise.

116
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,920
You asked me

117
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,840
how I feel about you.

118
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,960
To be honest, I don’t know.

119
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,320
I really don’t know

120
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:49,160
how I feel about you.

121
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,000
But this is what I know.

122
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,320
I don’t want to lose you.

123
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:05,560
I’m sorry.

124
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,560
Sorry for what this time?

125
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,120
You have apologized to me too many times.

126
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,440
I’m sorry for avoiding you.

127
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:15,720
I’m also sorry that…

128
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,560
Ko Song.

129
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,120
I promised you that
I wouldn’t disappear again.

130
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,360
You went to take a tutoring class.
You didn’t disappear.

131
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,840
Stop apologizing.

132
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,720
Let’s go back to being the same.

133
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:43,240
Smile.

134
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,080
Smile, Ko Song.

135
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,480
Why don’t you smile?

136
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:51,960
Will you smile or not?

137
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,080
Will you smile or not?

138
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:53,520
I’ll smile.

139
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:54,920
Will you smile or not?

140
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:55,880
Ouch.

141
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:56,840
Ouch.

142
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:58,000
Ouch.

143
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,920
Ko, Ko, Ko.

144
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,680
Mom.

145
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,120
Shh

146
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,360
That’s all.

147
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:17,280
Thank you.

148
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:20,680
Thank you.

149
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,080
It’s late. Why aren’t you sleeping?

150
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,280
You were soaked in the rain.
You may get sick.

151
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,800
I’ll go to bed soon.

152
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,480
Orange, you should go to bed,
or you may get sick.

153
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,840
I’m happy that we are now the same.

154
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:22,880
Bring me oranges tomorrow, my minion.

155
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,200
Yes, boss.

156
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,080
Good night, Ko Song.

157
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,000
Good night, Orange.

158
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:39,440
Ko.

159
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:40,160
Yes.

160
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:41,440
Why didn’t you go to school?

161
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:42,520
I have a cold.

162
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,120
Are you faking it?

163
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:49,920
No, I’m really sick.

164
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:52,000
If you don’t believe me,
do you want me to spread it to you?

165
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:54,560
Ko!

166
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,360
I believe you. Stop it.

167
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:59,240
You always pretend to be sick

168
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,480
when I ask you to go
and help me on the boat.

169
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,000
Did you get wet in the rain yesterday?

170
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,320
How did you know that?

171
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,480
I saw your friend also didn’t go to school.

172
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,040
Ko Song is home?

173
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,680
See? I knew it.

174
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,480
I saw him watering the plants
in front of his house.

175
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:19,760
Did you two plan this together?

176
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:21,440
I didn’t know anything about it.

177
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:23,920
I’m going in to get some sleep.

178
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:26,840
Dad.

179
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,240
Mom didn’t prepare a meal for you.

180
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:32,120
When you wake up,
you need to go out and buy it.

181
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:33,560
Ko.

182
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,120
You are home. Why don’t you buy it?

183
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,320
I’m sick.

184
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:40,080
It’s just an act.

185
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:08,760
Who are you looking for?

186
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:15,240
I…

187
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,200
I’m going to pick an orange.

188
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:23,640
Good job, my minion.

189
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:26,840
Here, eat it.

190
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:35,560
I have a cold.

191
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:37,280
Aren’t you afraid of being near me?

192
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,640
Me too.

193
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,720
Do you like oranges that much?

194
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:53,640
Always.

195
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:01,560
Eat it a lot.

196
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,840
Oranges have high vitamin C.

197
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,920
It’s good for a cold.

198
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,560
Then you should eat them too.

199
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,800
Let’s go out for a ride.

200
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,000
No.

201
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,280
We are sick.

202
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,800
We should be resting.

203
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:33,560
You are smart,
but how can you not know this?

204
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:38,920
Taking a ride is a kind of rest.

205
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:39,760
Come on.

206
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:42,000
Come on.

207
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:42,960
Orange.

208
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:14,960
August.

209
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,200
Why are you sitting here?

210
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:21,200
It’s none of your business.

211
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,520
Assh*le, I asked
because I’m worried about you.

212
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:38,360
Boss Ko.

213
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,680
Ko Song, woo!

214
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,320
You are sick and still so hyper.

215
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:21,400
We need to act like we weren’t sick
to confuse the virus.

216
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:24,760
One more thing, I ate a lot of vitamin C.

217
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:25,600
Look.

218
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:27,240
I got the orange power.

219
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,360
You just want an excuse to go out.

220
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:31,960
Uncle.

221
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:37,800
Uncle, are you here?
You have a customer waiting here.

222
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,440
Why don’t you come inside?

223
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,920
I want everything on the list.

224
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,200
So you two become loving.

225
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:55,320
I remember you two were always bickering.

226
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:58,520
Nonsense, Uncle.

227
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,720
Please go in and get things on my list.

228
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:02,920
I won’t tease you.

229
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:04,640
Come on.

230
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:24,680
Be gentle, Achi.

231
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,360
I told you not to overdo during the practice.

232
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,080
Why?

233
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,000
Are you worried about me?

234
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:33,480
You know what I mean.

235
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,840
- That must hurt.
- Will those two Ko come to school today?

236
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,440
Right.

237
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:41,400
How are things between them?

238
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:03,640
Thanks.

239
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:07,440
Hello, my friends. What are you doing?

240
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,720
Do you miss us?

241
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:11,760
Where have you been?

242
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,200
I was sick.

243
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:15,480
But I’m fine now.

244
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:19,640
Did you two make up?

245
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:22,640
Yes.

246
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:26,560
It was typical of Ko Neung.

247
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,760
He gets mad to get attention.

248
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,400
Nonsense, Augar.

249
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:34,520
I’m the most reasonable person in the world.

250
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:42,280
What happened to your knee?

251
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:46,520
What did you write on it?

252
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,400
A…

253
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,120
A…

254
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:01,840
A-eh-ya-eh-yah!

255
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:02,840
Why?

256
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:05,520
Huh?

257
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,840
You are reading Dragon Ball too much.

258
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:10,960
Yeah.

259
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,600
I’m really into it.

260
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:48,720
Tle.

261
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:55,440
Are you mad that I sat at Ko Neung’s desk
instead of sitting with you yesterday?

262
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,280
No.

263
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:03,920
I get it. You are probably confused
after knowing I wrote the notes.

264
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:08,000
You’re right.

265
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:10,680
I never thought
they came from the guy sitting next to me.

266
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:12,520
Right.

267
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,800
But I’m curious.

268
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,080
Why do you fall for a guy like me?

269
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:25,360
Why?

270
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,920
I am…

271
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:34,840
I don’t know.

272
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:37,400
I just like you.

273
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,840
I don’t need a reason for it.

274
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:47,760
You’re right.

275
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:53,080
I don’t expect you to like me back.

276
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,920
We can be friends like this.

277
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,920
August, bestie.

