When I got home, no one was there.

545
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:31,720
I haven’t eaten anything.

546
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,120
Did they tell you where they were going?

547
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:39,920
They left a note
saying they would be home late.

548
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,400
And they left some money.

549
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:46,480
Don’t need to say anything
to make me feel better.

550
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:48,160
I’m used to it.

551
00:40:49,520 --> 00:40:50,640
I know that.

552
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:56,200
But if it bothers you, you should talk to them.

553
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:00,120
Maybe later.

554
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:05,520
Are you ready for tomorrow?

555
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,960
Yes, I’m very ready

556
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:12,040
I’m looking forward to playing this character.

557
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:15,440
You are getting yourself into trouble.

558
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:19,120
You need to blame Tle for this.
He makes me do it.

559
00:41:20,120 --> 00:41:20,800
The role is perfect for you.

560
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:23,360
I think you know the person best.

561
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,080
You’re right.

562
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,760
I’m close with him.

563
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:28,480
Just kidding.

564
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:32,800
Here.

565
00:41:34,720 --> 00:41:36,680
A reward for a brave man.

566
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,000
Does it taste good?

567
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:49,240
Yes, but don’t need to give me another one.

568
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:51,400
Who is actually hungry here?

569
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:54,400
I’m going back to eating.

570
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:57,680
You can have my wonton.

571
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,920
The shop’s wontons are the highlight.

572
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:27,080
It’s delicious.

573
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:31,000
I told you the noodles here are the best.

574
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:53,760
Next is a play
performed by Grade 11 students.

575
00:42:54,160 --> 00:42:57,240
The title is ‘Teachers, We Are Sorry.”

576
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:19,960
Didn’t I tell you?

577
00:43:20,600 --> 00:43:22,720
If you are late, you will be punished.

578
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:26,240
Do 20 push-ups.

579
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,280
Do it now.

580
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:34,960
Good. You’re working together.

581
00:43:35,440 --> 00:43:36,960
I’ll help you too.

582
00:43:40,440 --> 00:43:41,400
What the heck are you doing?

583
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:42,600
You are scooping up water.

584
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:44,080
Are you kidding me?

585
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:46,040
Mr. Prateep.

586
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:48,680
These are students in my class.

587
00:43:50,240 --> 00:43:51,840
Can you let it slide this time?

588
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:53,840
Sure, Mr. Kong.

589
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:58,240
But don’t let it happen again.

590
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:02,400
Then Mr. Prateep would say.

591
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:06,600
Don’t let me see you do it again.

592
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:11,920
Teachers, we are sorry.

593
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:17,760
Why are you so noisy?

594
00:44:18,680 --> 00:44:20,480
Why are the Grade 12 students not here yet?

595
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:22,400
If they aren’t here, I’ll go take a nap.

596
00:44:32,400 --> 00:44:33,920
Mr. Chon.

597
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:38,160
Hello, Miss Peung.

598
00:44:40,680 --> 00:44:43,400
Why didn’t you say anything
when you walked in?

599
00:44:44,800 --> 00:44:46,560
You often complain about your back pain.

600
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:48,400
I brought you a muscle rub.

601
00:44:58,000 --> 00:44:59,160
Thank you.

602
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:04,720
Why do you need to come in and interrupt us?

603
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:08,200
I’m flirting with Mr. Chon.

604
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:14,800
Teachers, we are sorry.

605
00:45:14,840 --> 00:45:16,600
Why do you keep apologizing?

606
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:21,520
Don’t you know it’s bad to do that?

607
00:45:22,480 --> 00:45:27,040
It means you are making mistakes repeatedly.

608
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:28,840
Mr. Prateep.

609
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:32,720
No teacher would want to hear an apology
from their students.

610
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:37,680
We all want our students to grow up

611
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:41,040
to have a bright future and good goals in life.

612
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:44,440
We want you to have a stable career.

613
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:52,480
I hope that the Grade 12 students
will set a good example for their juniors.

614
00:45:53,960 --> 00:45:57,320
This school is just a small beginning.

615
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:03,280
I wish you all the best
on the path you’ve chosen.

616
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:09,040
As representatives of the Grade 11 students,

617
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:12,280
we would like to thank
and apologize to the teachers

618
00:46:13,040 --> 00:46:17,400
for all the good and bad things that we did.

619
00:46:43,720 --> 00:46:45,400
This is so embarrassing.

620
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:49,120
I won’t forget that Tle made me do this.

621
00:46:49,400 --> 00:46:50,920
You did a wonderful job, Augar.

622
00:46:51,720 --> 00:46:53,040
Why don’t you do it yourself?

623
00:46:54,040 --> 00:46:56,200
It would be easier to play Mr. Chon.

624
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:57,520
Then it wouldn’t be funny.

625
00:46:57,760 --> 00:46:59,400
I still have another year in this school.

626
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:00,880
How am I going to face others?

627
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,320
My teammates will tease me about it.

628
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:06,440
Augar, don’t worry. I’ll protect you.

629
00:47:06,480 --> 00:47:09,280
If someone teases you, I’ll punch them.

630
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:10,760
Are you going to do that?

631
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:11,160
Yes.

632
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:22,840
Oh, my eyes hurt.

633
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:25,760
The soap got into my eyes.

634
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:26,560
Which one?

635
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:01,400
How is it?

636
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:03,040
It’s better.

637
00:48:04,440 --> 00:48:06,000
Shall we go?

638
00:48:19,240 --> 00:48:20,440
I’ll help you.

639
00:48:22,960 --> 00:48:24,280
Yes, Mr. Kong.

640
00:48:26,840 --> 00:48:28,160
Do I look okay?

641
00:48:29,720 --> 00:48:30,360
Yes.

642
00:48:31,640 --> 00:48:32,960
You look really okay.

643
00:48:35,200 --> 00:48:39,640
Seriously, how did you come up
with the idea for the teacher parody?

644
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:44,200
Isn’t it what you and your friend are good at?

645
00:48:45,400 --> 00:48:46,760
Is that a compliment or criticism?

646
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:48,880
It’s a compliment.

647
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:52,280
You all did a great job today.

648
00:48:52,880 --> 00:48:56,440
August, you look cute
when dressing like this.

649
00:49:04,120 --> 00:49:06,960
Didn’t your friends go to have lunch?

650
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:08,920
Why didn’t you go with them?

651
00:49:09,760 --> 00:49:11,120
Yeah, you’re right.

652
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:13,000
I haven’t had lunch.

653
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:15,840
You should go.

654
00:49:23,760 --> 00:49:24,920
Why don’t you come
and have lunch with me?

655
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:28,320
I still have to clean up here.

656
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:31,440
No, I mean another day.

657
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:32,360
Do you want to have a meal with me?

658
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:38,400
Sure.

659
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:42,600
Okay. I’ve got to go.

660
00:49:42,800 --> 00:49:44,160
Okay. Bye.

661
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:49,320
Promise?

662
00:49:50,480 --> 00:49:52,040
Yes, I promise.

663
00:50:04,560 --> 00:50:06,040
You did well today, Orange.

664
00:50:06,040 --> 00:50:07,520
This is the first time I saw this side of you.

665
00:50:08,760 --> 00:50:10,240
Did I really do well?

666
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:11,560
Of course.

667
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:15,000
So I deserve a reward, right?

668
00:50:15,880 --> 00:50:17,360
You’re getting used to it, aren’t you?

669
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:20,680
If I do well, I should be rewarded, right?

670
00:50:22,680 --> 00:50:23,440
What do you want?

671
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:36,120
What about oranges?

672
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:39,560
It’s too simple.

673
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:45,200
What about…?

674
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:47,280
I’ll buy you an ice cream.

675
00:50:47,800 --> 00:50:48,600
No.

676
00:50:56,880 --> 00:50:58,040
What about this?

677
00:50:59,440 --> 00:51:00,800
Do you want to come to my room
to play games?

678
00:51:07,560 --> 00:51:10,360
(I don’t know why I said that.)

679
00:51:12,120 --> 00:51:15,600
(Maybe it’s because I’ve never wanted
to go back to the way we were.)

680
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:23,000
(Maybe because my brain is overthinking,
so my heart takes over.)

681
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:31,000
(Or maybe because I want to kiss him again,
intentionally this time.)

682
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:48,880
(But what I really want is that
he feels the same way as I do.)

683
00:51:50,520 --> 00:51:54,160
♪ Will say "I love you" ♪

684
00:51:54,960 --> 00:51:59,520
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

685
00:51:59,520 --> 00:52:04,000
♪ No more watching from afar,
letting chances go ♪

686
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:07,200
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

687
00:52:07,200 --> 00:52:11,120
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪

688
00:52:13,040 --> 00:52:15,720
- When you like someone, you want to tease them.

689
00:52:15,760 --> 00:52:16,040
- Boo!

690
00:52:16,160 --> 00:52:18,120
- Why did you hit my butt?

691
00:52:18,200 --> 00:52:21,200
- You should watch and see
if that person likes to hit your butt.

692
00:52:21,960 --> 00:52:24,160
- Ko Song, I want to eat an orange.

693
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:41,240
- Every time I have a problem,
you are a light for me.

